The word ‘essential’ has never held as much meaning as right now. That's according to a nurse on his first day under South Africa’s 21-day-lockdown.#21daylockdownSA #Day1 #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The word ‘essential’ has never held as much meaning as right now. That's according to a nurse on his first day under South Africa’s 21-day lockdown. READ: Health workers express concern over lack of protective gear Healthcare workers form part of an essential service, and therefore have to continue fighting the good fight while others stay at home. Soldiers may be patrolling the country's streets, but it's people like Rich Sicina who are engaged in the frontline battles. * eNCA reporter Masego Rahlaga spent some time with Sicina, who is a professional nurse. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.